modules.description: This module implements an IPv4 layer that handles packet demultiplexing, transmission, and source address selection. It processes incoming IP frames with provided TCP, UDP, or default protocol handlers, sends packets with configurable fragmentation and TTL, and computes pseudoheaders for checksums. It works with IP addresses, prefixes, and Ethernet frames, and is used to manage network communication over IPv4 in a QubesDB context.

This module provides IPv4 networking capabilities, handling packet demultiplexing, transmission, and source address selection. It processes incoming IP frames using TCP, UDP, or custom protocol handlers, supports configurable TTL and fragmentation during packet sending, and computes pseudoheaders for checksums. Key data types include IP addresses, prefixes, and Ethernet frames. Example usage includes routing incoming packets to the appropriate protocol handler and constructing outgoing IP packets with specified source and destination addresses.
